Description: Unique identifier for each billboard.
GPS latitude (WGS84) of the billboard location (in decimal degrees).
GPS longitude (WGS84) of the billboard location (in decimal degrees).
Municipality name in Puerto Rico (e.g., San Juan, Carolina).
Road prefixed name in Puerto Rico (e.g. PR22)
Orientation of the billboard relative to traffic flow: Inbound, Outbound or Alternative which is placed on building sides
Daily Effective Circulation: estimated average daily audience per day (vehicles occupancy).
Cost-Per-Mille: advertising cost in USD per 1,000 impressions, based on DEC.
Billboard face area in square feet.
Monthly rental price of the billboard in USD (target variable).
Prime location indicator: Yes for high-visibility/high-traffic, No otherwise.
